  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6773.32 sitting below the 6799 GEX flip in PIN regime, dealers are long gamma and actively buying this dip while providing stabilizing flow. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (53.5B) creates strong resistance where dealers will aggressively sell rallies, while the negative gamma at 6770 (-35.6B) offers support where dealers buy dips and shorts cover. The recent GEX surge combined with spot trading between these key levels suggests dealers are managing large hedging flows, with 6770-6800 becoming the primary trading range.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect choppy price action with strong support at 6770 and resistance at 6800.",
